  "commentary": "With SPX at 7007.52 sitting just above the massive 7000 gamma wall (19.9B), dealers are likely selling into this recent strength as they're long gamma and need to fade the move. The thick positive gamma cluster from 7000-7100 creates a strong magnet effect that should cap upside momentum and pull price back toward these key strikes. Watch 7000 as the critical pivot - a break below triggers dealer buying support, while sustained action above keeps dealers as natural sellers into any rallies toward 7025-7050.\n\nBottom line: expect price to get pulled back toward 7000 and chop around these big gamma levels.",
